♪♪

09:19.000 --> 09:21.000
There's lots over here.

09:21.000 --> 09:25.000
Ugh!

09:21.000 --> 09:25.000
It's too hot to be outside.

09:25.000 --> 09:27.000
This one

09:25.000 --> 09:27.000
looks like a snake.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.000
Thanks.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
Child:

09:32.000 --> 09:34.000
Other stuff burns, too!

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
Where do you want us

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
to pile it?

09:40.000 --> 09:42.000
That won't burn.

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
There's too much life

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
in it.

09:44.000 --> 09:46.000
The best firewood

09:44.000 --> 09:46.000
is dead wood.

09:46.000 --> 09:48.000
It's not for burning.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.000
It's for something else.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.000
Stick people.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.000
Nope.

09:52.000 --> 09:55.000
I'm too old

09:52.000 --> 09:55.000
for that stuff.

09:55.000 --> 09:56.000
What, then?

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
I want it

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
to be a surprise.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.000
[ Grunts ]

10:10.000 --> 10:13.000
Paul: You don't have to bury

10:10.000 --> 10:13.000
the creature's bones.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
I told you, Campion.

10:15.000 --> 10:18.000
Animals don't

10:15.000 --> 10:18.000
have souls.

10:18.000 --> 10:21.000
Just because you say it

10:18.000 --> 10:21.000
doesn't make it true.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.000
I didn't make it up.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.000
My father told me

10:23.000 --> 10:25.000
when I was very little.

10:25.000 --> 10:27.000
It's a fact.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.000
How did your father know?

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
He read it

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
in the scriptures.

10:30.000 --> 10:32.000
And how did the person

10:30.000 --> 10:32.000
who wrote the scriptures know?

10:32.000 --> 10:36.000
I don't know, Campion.

10:32.000 --> 10:36.000
But now you're being annoying.

10:36.000 --> 10:38.000
I think everything

10:36.000 --> 10:38.000
has a soul.

10:38.000 --> 10:41.000
Even Mother and Father.

10:41.000 --> 10:43.000
Maybe even trees.

10:45.000 --> 10:46.000
The big ones, anyway.

10:46.000 --> 10:49.000
That's such a babyish thing

10:46.000 --> 10:49.000
to say.

10:49.000 --> 10:52.000
I don't mind disagreeing

10:49.000 --> 10:52.000
with you, Paul.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
You can disagree

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
and still be friends.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
Mother and Father

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
are always disagreeing,

10:56.000 --> 10:58.000
and they're still friends.

10:58.000 --> 11:00.000
I don't mind, either.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
You believe what you want to,

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
Campion.

11:05.000 --> 11:07.000
I think these wood-gathering

11:05.000 --> 11:07.000
trips would be more beneficial

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
if someone besides me

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
actually gathered some wood.

11:11.000 --> 11:14.000
So did you find out where she's

11:11.000 --> 11:14.000
been running to all this time?

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
You're referring to my private

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
conversation with Mother?

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
Yeah.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
You know humans usually end up

11:18.000 --> 11:21.000
leaving each other

11:18.000 --> 11:21.000
over stuff like that.

11:21.000 --> 11:23.000
Like what?

11:21.000 --> 11:23.000
I don't know,

11:21.000 --> 11:23.000
when their partner lies to them.

11:23.000 --> 11:24.000
Mother is not lying.

11:25.000 --> 11:26.000
[ Chuckles ]

11:26.000 --> 11:27.000
If you were

11:26.000 --> 11:27.000
a little sharper,

11:27.000 --> 11:29.000
maybe she wouldn't get over

11:27.000 --> 11:29.000
on you so much.

11:29.000 --> 11:30.000
My offer still stands,

11:29.000 --> 11:30.000
you know.

11:30.000 --> 11:32.000
I could give you

11:30.000 --> 11:32.000
a little tune-up --

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
boost your processing power.

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
Every little bit counts.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.000
Carry these.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.000
[ Grunts ]

